      1.Python is interpreted as well as compiled language also
      2.but in high level python is an interpreted language it will compiled internally to bytecode before execution.
      3.python internally convert source code(.py) to byte code compiled(.pyc files)
      4.when we trigger python function first it will convert source file to byte code and then compiled byte code is executed by using  python virtual machines(PVM)
      Python is Interpreted because:
        No separate compile step is needed
        run the code line-by-line at runtime
        easier debugging
        platform independent

