c = Cat()  # ✅ Works

If a class inherits from an abstract class, it MUST implement all abstract methods.

Abstract Class:
    An abstract class is a class that cannot be instantiated and is used as a blueprint. It contains abstract methods (methods without implementation) that must be implemented by child classes.

Abstract Method:
    A method declared without implementation that forces child classes to define its behavior.

Why This Concept Exists(Important Insight)?
