    Async web applications

It is built on:

    Starlette → async web layer
    Pydantic → validation layer

2. Async Endpoints — Deep Explanation

    An async endpoint allows the server to handle other requests while waiting for slow operations.

    Example slow operations:

        Database calls
        External API calls
        File uploads
        Redis calls
        Kafka events

Synchronous Problem:

    @app.get("/users")
    def get_users():
        data = requests.get("https://external-api.com")
        return data.json()

    Problem:
        Thread gets blocked
        Cannot serve other users
        Poor scalability

Async Solution:
    @app.get("/users")
    async def get_users():
        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:
            response = await client.get("https://external-api.com")
        return response.json()

    Now:

        Request pauses during waiting
        Event loop handles other users
        Better throughput

Real-Time Example
    Food Delivery App

    User opens app:

        Backend simultaneously does:

            Fetch restaurants
            Fetch offers
            Fetch delivery partner
            Fetch live location
            Fetch recommendations

    Without async:
        Slow

    With async:
        All operations happen concurrently
---------------------------------------------------------------
Q: Difference between concurrency and parallelism?

    Concurrency means:

        Multiple tasks make progress together.

    Parallelism means:

        Multiple tasks execute literally at the same time using multiple CPU cores.

    Real Example
    Concurrency

        Restaurant waiter handling many tables.

    Parallelism

        5 chefs cooking simultaneously.

-----------------------------------------------------------------
Why FastAPI over Flask?

    FastAPI provides:

        native async support
        automatic validation
        OpenAPI docs
        better type safety
        higher performance

    Flask is lightweight but requires additional libraries for these capabilities.

---------------------------------------------------------------------
When should NOT use async?

    Avoid async for CPU-bound operations like:

        image processing
        AI model training
        video encoding

    Because CPU tasks block event loop.

    Use:

        worker queues
        multiprocessing
        distributed workers
------------------------------------------------------------------------
How do you scale FastAPI?

    Horizontal scaling:

        Multiple containers
        Kubernetes pods
        Load balancer

    Performance improvements:

        Redis caching
        Async DB drivers
        Connection pooling
        CDN
        Background workers
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Explain event loop simply

    The event loop is the scheduler that manages async tasks.

        When one task waits for I/O:

        loop switches to another task

    This allows high concurrency using fewer threads.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
How do you design production-grade APIs?

I focus on:

    REST standards
    validation
    security
    idempotency
    pagination
    observability
    rate limiting
    versioning
    backward compatibility
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q6: How do you handle failures in async APIs?

    Use:

    retries
    circuit breakers
    timeouts
    fallback responses
    structured logging
    distributed tracing

